@Barry Ancona I know you enjoy your stone tablet, but on the app, with overlays off, and not clicking the circled “i”  to show the title (my preferred practice), I had a pretty fun solving experience. I still had circles in my grid, but no scissors. Once I filled 23 across, the circle element of the puzzle was easily deduced. I also quickly determined that extra letters were needed in some other answers, but they were not explicitly flagged by their corresponding clues.  Once I got to the revealer (organically), the conceit became clear. The locations of the missing “once”es were fairly easy to figure out, but at least not explicitly given. 

On the whole, I thought this puzzle was a great example of the benefit of solving with overlays off - for someone who enjoys figuring out the extra trickery without hints 🤓.

Even with overlays off, I finished well under my average time for a Sunday puzzle - but it was still fun to figure out.

